{"ts":"2026-06-26T16:10:27.370Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Investigating Build Errors**\n\nI'm currently looking into the timeout errors I'm encountering with `npm run build` and `npm run lint`. It seems the default 30-second timeout of `run_commands` isn't sufficient for Next.js builds on standard setups. I'm exploring quicker checks for compilation or type errors to circumvent this issue.\n\n\n**Analyzing Preflight Checklist**\n\nI've moved on to the preflight audit checklist, specifically for the \"Build With GFF tools\" interactive build phase 3. I'm verifying the requirements, reviewing recent changes as a senior UI/UX and frontend quality reviewer, and assessing the UI against the quality bar. I'm taking a look at each tool, starting with the ROI Calculator, Asset Marketplace, Readiness Assessor, Foundry Studio Simulator, Proposal Studio, Sandbox Simulator, and Blueprint Generator, checking their components and functionality, with manual checks.\n\n\n**Defining New Feature Set**\n\nI'm now focusing on a new feature set. I'm prioritizing validation controls, including custom select inputs and a multiselect for strategic priorities. I'm also exploring an interactive pin suggestion system with validation (code: 123456) and a dynamic SVG score dial. I am designing personalized solutions matched to custom selections and a 90-day implementation roadmap timeline. I've confirmed that the landing page remains untouched and no slug routing is present. There's no backend/API/AWS/auth/OTP/export behavior either.\n\n\n**Confirming Pure Client-Side States**\n\nI've verified that all interactive elements are using pure, premium client-side states, ensuring zero database dependencies and adherence to project guardrails. I've also confirmed the absence of any external logos, metrics, or client files, with local state-triggered download simulations. The UI design is consistent and premium, built with standard components and a dark space-grade layout, and is fully mobile responsive.\n\n\n"}}
